The paper focuses on the use of deep learning for obstacle detection and tracking in autonomous driving, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of synthetic data and simulation is also a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the practical application of the proposed method in large-scale industrial settings suggests a potential fit with systems and control (cs.SY).
